@page
@{
    Layout = "_Layout";
    ViewData["Title"] = "Employ mentors";
}

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
        <a href="/" data-testid="home-link" class="govuk-back-link">Home</a>
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l" data-testid="academic-mentors-header">Employ an academic mentor</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You can employ an academic mentor for a year at a time as a salaried member of staff. They’ll work alongside
            teaching staff and provide 1 to 1 and small-group sessions (no more than 6 pupils).
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            There are 2 ways to find an academic mentor.
        </p>
        <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-!-margin-left-4">
            <li>
                <a href="https://www.ntpacademicmentors.co.uk/schools/register-your-school" target="_blank" class="govuk-link" data-testid="cognition-registration-link">Register with Cognition</a>, the central provider, to be matched with a suitable academic mentor.
                They’re likely to be a recent graduate, a school leaver taking a gap year, or someone considering a career in teaching or education.
            </li>
            <li>Select and appoint someone directly.</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            Academic mentors will be allocated from the central pool on the basis of suitability and proximity. If there
            are more requests than people, schools with the greatest proportion of pupil premium-eligible pupils will be
            given priority.
        </p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-l" data-testid="training-academic-header">Training for academic mentors you appoint</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            New academic mentors must complete intensive training before they start work. This online course is spread
            over 1 to 2 weeks. You can request that they take additional modules in relevant topics.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            Use the Education Development Trust service to <a href="http://nominations.tutortraining.co.uk/registration" target="_blank"
                                                              class="govuk-link" data-testid="book-training">book training for your academic mentor</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m" data-testid="renewing-contract-header">
            Training for academic mentors you’ve employed
            before
        </h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            If you’re renewing the contract of an academic mentor you employed in 2021 to 2022, they don’t need to
            repeat
            the whole course. But you can request they take a refresher module.
        </p>
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-l" data-testid="employment-terms-header">Employment terms</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You need to employ your academic mentor to the end of the 2022 to 2023 academic year, including all school
            holidays.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            If you’re a small school, you can share an academic mentor with other schools in your academy trust or local
            area.
        </p>
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m" data-testid="salary-onboarding-header">Salary and onboarding costs</h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You’re responsible for onboarding costs and paying the academic mentor’s salary. This will be a minimum of:
        </p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-!-margin-left-4">
            <li>£21,000 if they have a degree</li>
            <li>£19,000 if they do not have a degree</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            Your funding allocation will cover a proportion of their salary (up to 60%). For more details and examples
            <a href="/funding-and-reporting" data-testid="funding-allocation-link" class="govuk-link">
                read the
                information on funding.
            </a>
        </p>
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-l" data-testid="employment-terms-header">Checks you need to do</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You must carry out the following checks on new academic mentors:
        </p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-!-margin-left-4">
            <li>references</li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://www.gov.uk/find-out-dbs-check/y/caring-for-or-working-with-children-under-18-or-working-in-a-school/teaching-or-caring-for-children/working-in-a-school-nursery-children-s-centre-or-home-detention-service-young-offender-institution-or-childcare-premises/yes"
                   target="_blank" data-testid="dbs-check-link" class="govuk-link">DBS enhanced check with barred lists</a>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-third">
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Find out how much funding you’ll get</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body"><a asp-page="/FundingAndReporting" data-testid="funding-reporting-link" class="govuk-link">Funding and reporting</a></p>
    </div>
</div>